build:
STACK: plain ES modules served from GitHub Pages (modules work with no build step; no CDN — everything vendored/hand-rolled). New surface dir rapp-go/ :
  rapp-go/items.js       — ITEMS table + DROP_TABLES (pure data + a weightedDraw helper)
  rapp-go/overpass.js    — Overpass fetch + tile cache (IndexedDB 'rapp-go'/'tiles')
  rapp-go/store.js       — inventory + poi-state + lures (localStorage), bag cap, prune
  rapp-go/geo.js         — geohashEncode/Decode + haversine (geohash copied verbatim from hologram/index.html L492/1007; add haversine)
  rapp-go/rng.js         — mkRng (copied verbatim from hologram/index.html L722)
  rapp-go/poi-power.js   — orchestrator exporting the public API above; imports the four
  rapp-go/index.html     — Explorer shell (map lives in a sibling system; for MVP a distance-sorted "nearby" list + bag drawer)

OVERPASS (respecting policy):
  Endpoint list w/ failover: ['https://overpass-api.de/api/interpreter','https://overpass.kumi.systems/api/interpreter'] (both send CORS headers). POST, body = 'data='+encodeURIComponent(ql).
  TILING = coarse location by design (privacy + cache + rate): tileId = geohashEncode(lat,lng,6). bbox = tile-center ± (0.006° lat, 0.008° lng) (~650 m box; overlaps neighbors so edges are covered). Only fetch on a tile MISS or expiry; prefetch a neighbor when the player crosses into a new geohash6. TTL 14 days (POIs rarely move). Throttle: ≥8 s between any two Overpass requests (a module-level lastFetch clock + a queue); timeout 25 s; on 429/5xx exponential backoff then try the mirror, then degrade to cached/empty (incense/lure-only mode) — never spam.
  QL (node-focused, bounded payload):
    [out:json][timeout:25];
    ( node["amenity"~"^(drinking_water|fountain|cafe|library|townhall|marketplace|clock|place_of_worship|bench)$"](S,W,N,E);
      node["tourism"~"^(artwork|attraction|viewpoint|museum|gallery|information)$"](S,W,N,E);
      node["historic"](S,W,N,E);
      node["natural"~"^(tree|spring|peak|rock)$"](S,W,N,E);
      node["leisure"~"^(park|garden)$"](S,W,N,E);
      way["tourism"="artwork"](S,W,N,E); );
    out center 200;
  Normalize each element → POI (classify() maps tags→kind), keep name (tags.name || humanized tag), store {tileId,fetchedAt,pois,attribution:'© OpenStreetMap contributors'}.

SPIN: spinPOI() → guard(inRange,ready) → seed=mkRng(poi.id+':'+state.n) → for each of draws(kind)(+bonus roll) weightedDraw(DROP_TABLES[kind], seed) → aggregate → store.grant(each) (respect BAG cap: overflow items are dropped with a gentle "bag full" note) → state.poi[poi.id]={t:Date.now(), n:state.n+1} → return drops.
HAVERSINE: standard R=6371000 formula for range checks (with slack = min(pos.accuracy, 25 m)).
No third-party JS; the raster map + AR are sibling surfaces — this module ships headless-testable (drive it from index.html list UI or console).
